      "notes": "\"La gran aventura de David Santiso\" is a classic-style point-and-click \r\nadventure game set in Spain, with adult humor and social satire in the \r\ntradition of the old Sierra games.\r\n\r\nAdult content present in the game:\r\n- General adult humor (not sexually explicit).\r\n- Cartoon-style violence: comedic fights and slapstick, no gore, no blood.\r\n- References to alcohol consumption (Asturian cider and other drinks) as \r\n  part of the cultural setting (bars, taverns).\r\n- Satirical references to ayahuasca and other recreational substances in \r\n  a humorous context. No promotion of drug use.\r\n- Occasional coarse language typical of colloquial Spanish.\r\n\r\nNote for the Steam review team:\r\nOne of the secondary characters is an influencer identified as a \r\nnational-socialist. She is presented as part of a satirical critique of \r\ncontemporary Spanish society: the game emphasizes that, although the \r\nprotagonist openly denounces her ideology, the rest of the characters \r\nand her followers keep inviting her to events as if nothing happened. \r\nThe narrative intent is to criticize social tolerance of extremism, not \r\nto promote it. No Nazi symbols, salutes, or apologia appear in the game.\r\n"
